commit 6fa71e23c6be3c06adf0ce134430e08efd849d25
Author: Tal Galili <tal.galili@gmail.com>
Date:   Thu Feb 28 16:58:19 2013 +0200

    Added the update.R function.
    
    This function checks for a newer version of R, and if it exists - it downloads it.
    
    I seperated this function to its own .r file, which also contain a bunch of other functions such as
    install.R - for installing R.
    check.for.updates.R - for checking if a newer version of R exists.
    And turn.version.to.number - which turns a version character (like 2.15.2) to a number which allows  the comparison between versions.

